<body>
    <div class="safety-container">
        <h1>Safety at University Management System</h1>
        <p>Ensuring the safety of our students, faculty, and staff is a top priority at the University Management System. We adhere to strict safety standards and practices to provide a secure environment for everyone.</p>

        <h2>Our Safety Commitments:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Regular Inspections:</strong> Our facilities undergo regular inspections and maintenance to ensure they meet safety standards.</li>
            <li><strong>Trained Staff:</strong> Our staff members are well-trained in safety procedures and emergency response to handle any situation effectively.</li>
            <li><strong>Clear Signage:</strong> Safety signs and instructions are prominently displayed throughout our campus for easy visibility and understanding.</li>
            <li><strong>Emergency Equipment:</strong> We are equipped with the necessary emergency response equipment, including fire extinguishers, first aid kits, and automated external defibrillators (AEDs).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Safety Tips for Students and Staff:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Be aware of your surroundings and report any suspicious activity to campus security.</li>
            <li>Follow all posted safety signs and instructions on campus.</li>
            <li>In case of an emergency, follow the evacuation plan and use the nearest exit.</li>
            <li>Familiarize yourself with the location of emergency equipment such as fire extinguishers and first aid kits.</li>
            <li>Attend safety training sessions provided by the university to stay informed about safety procedures.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Your safety is important to us. If you have any concerns or questions regarding safety on campus, please feel free to contact our safety office.</p>
    </div>
</body>
